Extract Bus Data from API¶

This python notebook uses API from webservices provided by nextbus.com in order to download, extract and store the data about the current bus network deployed in cities in local files to be used for further analysis afterward.

In [1]: 
import requests
import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET
import pandas as pd

url = 'http://webservices.nextbus.com/service/publicXMLFeed?command=agencyList';
r = requests.get(url);

def extractData(nodeName, r):
    root = ET.fromstring(r.text);
    data =  {}
    for node in root.iter(nodeName):
        for key in node.attrib:
            if key not in data:
                data[key] = [];
            data[key].append(node.attrib[key]);
    maxLen = 0;
    for key in data:
        if maxLen < len(data[key]):
            maxLen = len(data[key]);
    toRemove = [];
    for key in data:
        if len(data[key]) < maxLen:
            toRemove.append(key);
    for key in toRemove:
        del data[key];
    df = pd.DataFrame(data);
    return df;

df = extractData("agency", r);
df.to_csv("/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/extra/agencyList.csv");
df.head(5)

Retrieve the data from all the routes currently in use in San Francisco by Muni:

In [3]: 
import xml.dom.minidom

url = "http://webservices.nextbus.com/service/publicXMLFeed?command=routeConfig&a=sf-muni&r=";

for tag in df['tag']:
    r = requests.get(url + tag);
    xmlResult = xml.dom.minidom.parseString(r.text)
    f = open("/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/extra/route_sf-muni_" + tag + ".xml", 'w');
    f.write(xmlResult.toprettyxml());
    f.close();

Transform xml files into data frames

In [10]: 
import re
index = []; # stopId, example: 13941
data = {
    "tag" : [], # example: 30
    "title" : [], # example: "Chestnut St &amp; Fillmore St"
    "lat" : [], # example: 37.8009099
    "lon" : [] # example: -122.43618
}

tmpIndex = [];
tmp = {
    "direction" : [],
    "order" : [],
}

for filename in os.listdir("/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/extra/"):
    if (re.search("^route.*\.xml", filename)):
        f = open("/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/extra/" + filename, "r");
        root = ET.parse(f);
        for route in root.iter("route"):
            tag = route.attrib['tag'];
            for direction in route.iter("direction"):
                i = 0;
                directionTitle = direction.attrib['title']
                for stop in direction.iter("stop"):
                    tmpIndex.append(stop.attrib['tag']);
                    tmp['direction'].append(directionTitle);
                    tmp['order'].append(i);
                    i += 1;
            for stop in route.iter("stop"):
                if "title" in stop.attrib:
                    index.append(stop.attrib['tag']);
                    data['tag'].append(tag);
                    data['title'].append(stop.attrib['title']);
                    data['lat'].append(stop.attrib['lat']);
                    data['lon'].append(stop.attrib['lon']);
        
dfTmp = pd.DataFrame(tmp, index=tmpIndex);   
df = pd.DataFrame(data, index=index);
df = pd.merge(df, dfTmp, left_index=True, right_index=True);
df.to_csv('/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/bus.csv');
df.head(5)

In [26]: 
import json

busLineData = []

for filename in os.listdir("/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/extra/"):
    if (re.search("^route.*\.xml", filename)):
        f = open("/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/extra/" + filename, "r");
        root = ET.parse(f);
        for route in root.iter("route"):
            tag = route.attrib['tag'];
            routeData = {}
            routeData['tag'] = tag;
            pathData = [];
            for path in route.iter("path"):
                segmentData = [];
                for point in path.iter("point"):
                    segmentData.append([point.attrib['lat'], point.attrib['lon']]);
                pathData.append(segmentData);
            routeData['path'] = pathData;
            busLineData.append(routeData);

f = open("/data1/home/christophe/dataviz/data/busLinePath.json", 'w');
f.write(json.dumps(busLineData, indent=1));
f.close();
